    <AbstractNarration>The Department of Applied Mathematics at the Illinois Institute of Technology will purchase a customized Linux cluster which will be dedicated to the support of research in the mathematical sciences. The equipment will be used for several research projects, including in particular:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;1. Further Development of the W-Curve as a Visualization and analytic Tool for the study of Long Genomic sequences, by Douglas J. Cork and F.R. McMorris;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;2. Numerical simulation of stochastic Partial Differential Equations in Fluid Dynamics, by Jinqiao Duan;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;3. Parallel algorithms for Meshless Methods, by Gregory Fasshauer;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;4. Numerical Investigations of Interfacial Dynamics in Fluid Dynamics, by Xiaofan Li.</AbstractNarration>
